From Red Herring Subject Re Clinton's immunization program In article PA David Veal writes In article Red Herring writes In article Jeffrey S Linder writes In article mwilson OM Mark Wilson writes On the news last night Clinton was bashing the republicans for stonewalling his so called stimulus It seems that one small item within this package was going to pay for free immunizations for poor Immunizations for children in this country are already free if you care to go have it The problem is not the cost it is the irresponible parents who are to stupid or to lazy to have it In case you haven't noticed Clintonites are pushing a universal health care ACCESS Access here means that folks who do not give a damn about immunizing their children will have health care services delivered to their I've read about more than a few of these programs that ran into problems in convincing parents to get their children immunized even when they were delivered to their I don't know maybe that sheet they have to be informed of about possible risks side effects and bad reactions scares The immunization program is just a useful first step Among other things the money will go to pay for creating and maintaning a a computerized innoculation database on all code named Big Just kidding the name will be Children Defense Database or something like Once the money is spent and little or no tangible results achieved the goverment will have to start knocking down doors in some neigborhoods and bribe parents in others probably the ones that are paying kids for attending the school what a fantastic idea David Veal of of Education Services Group PA I still remember the way you laughed the day your pushed me down the elevator shaft I'm beginning to think you don't love me Weird Al Disclaimer Opinions expressed are mine not my employer'